    "introBadge": "About the Community",
    "introHeading": "A safer site, built by managers and workers together",
    "introBody1": "The Occupational Safety & Health Community is an information-sharing platform where managers and workers from construction, manufacturing, and other industrial sites communicate openly. It offers Q&A, knowledge sharing, accident cases, near-miss reports, and anonymous tips — helping managers understand workers' real challenges and helping workers understand managers' legal duties and safety standards.",
    "introBody2": "In particular, anonymous reporting lets users surface site hazards without pressure. Mentions of company names, individual names, and site names are prohibited so the goal stays on improving safety culture rather than blaming. The platform aims to be a place where managers and workers understand each other's positions and raise the safety bar together."
